import React from 'react'

const StarIcon = () => {
    return (
        <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="18"
            height="17"
            viewBox="0 0 18 17"
        >
            <g fill="none" fillRule="evenodd" stroke="none" strokeWidth="1">
                <g transform="translate(-273 -4323)">
                    <g transform="translate(100 4266)">
                        <g transform="translate(170 54)">
                            <path fillRule="nonzero" d="M0 0L24 0 24 24 0 24z"></path>
                            <path className='star'
                                fill="#1D1D1D"
                                d="M12 17.27l4.15 2.51c.76.46 1.69-.22 1.49-1.08l-1.1-4.72 3.67-3.18c.67-.58.31-1.68-.57-1.75l-4.83-.41-1.89-4.46c-.34-.81-1.5-.81-1.84 0L9.19 8.63l-4.83.41c-.88.07-1.24 1.17-.57 1.75l3.67 3.18-1.1 4.72c-.2.86.73 1.54 1.49 1.08l4.15-2.5z"
                            ></path>
                        </g>
                    </g>
                </g>
            </g>
        </svg>
    )
}

export default StarIcon
